inn1.comm: angled into the pads and McCullum missed out as it takes him on the front pad and rolls to square leg
angled into leg stump again and it carries on down leg and called wide
full in at the pads and McCullum clips it to Bollinger at fine leg
better channel from Harris and he draws Guptill forward into a defensive shot and he drops it just beside the stumps

back of a length in at Guptill's hip and he clips it behind square, he calls wait then yes and McCullum would've been short of his ground had the throw hit. The backing up isn't in place and it goes for four overthrows
fuller this time and McCullum drives back to the bowler
back of a length outside off and McCullum pushes off the outside half of the blade to point
Bollinger goes full to test the swing and it's a half volley ouside off and Guptil cracks it through the covers for four
full on leg and Guptill whips it to square leg
good channel outside off and Guptill allows it through to the keeper
back of a length and Guptill moves back and defends with soft hands to point
fuller and wider of off stump again and Guptill shoulders' arms
good channel from Bollinger again and Guptill is happy to let it go
cracking delivery from Harris as he angles into off stump and then beats McCullum as it nips away from the bat
identical again from Harris hitting the corridor of uncertainty and McCullum is beaten again
back of a length closer to off stump and McCullum is back and defending back along the pitch
good length outside off and McCullum tries to push into the off side but it takes the inside half of the bat and back along the pitch to the bowler
back of a length of off and McCullum plays back and a touch too early and squirts it back to the bowler trying to play into the on side
great channel again to finish and McCullum sees it clearly and plays with the fuller face of the bat into the off side field
great delivery from Bollinger has Guptill hanging on the crease and playing away from his body, it takes the outside edge and flies through the vacant second slip region for four
back of a length and Guptill plays strongly to short cover
full on leg stump and Guptill whips it through forward square leg in the air just past Hopes at square leg and they get three to the long boundary
back of a length and outside off, McCullum chops it down into the ground and nearly back onto his stumps as we've already seen him do twice in the series
around the wicket and just too short as McCullum pulls through square leg, beating Hopes in the deep who had just moved back to the fence
back of a length and into McCullum's hip, he moves back and works it into the leg side for an easy single
McCullum advances down the track and hammers it straight out of the middle through cover for four
Harris drops short and McCullum is back and pulling over the short boundary at fine leg for six into the construction site
Harris is back into the channel and McCullum is back and across and playing into the off side with a straight bat
back of a length on off and McCullum moves back and defends back along the pitch
Harris loses his line and angles into the pads and McCullum clips him through mid wicket for three
good channel and Guptill defends with a slightly open face to cover
Bollinger oversteps and hits a good channel as McCullum pushes back to the bowler. Free-hit coming up...
another foot fault from Bollinger and McCullum picks it up and deposits it over fine leg for six
better length and McCullum tries to muscle it over the off side, he gets it high on the blade and Ponting takes the catch at mid off as they take the single from the free-hit
good length and Guptill drives back at the bowler
Bollinger provides Guptill with a juicy half volley and he pumps it over cover for four
better length outside off and Guptill plays to short cover
half volley on off stump and Guptill drives to mid off without the usual ping off the bat
half volley on off stump and Guptill drives wide of Ponting at mid off for a quick single
full outside off stump and Guptill drives through the covers and Hussey tidies up to keep the scoring to one
full and wide again but McCullum makes him pay as he hits underneath the ball and over cover point for four
half volley just outside off and McCullum drives to Voges at backward point
Johnson hits his length and beats McCullum who pushes at it outside off, super delivery
shorter this time and McCullum moves back and tries to work it into the leg side but he gets a leading edge into the on side and it drops just in front of Johnson in his follow through
good length on off stump and McCullum is back and defending into the off side, taking one hand off the bat
Watson immediately hits his length drawing Guptill forward and defending into the off side
fuller this time and Guptill stands tall and drives strongly through extra cover for four, glorious from the man with two toes on one foot
full and angled into leg stump and Guptill clips it over mid wicket for four runs, good stroke

Watson is full again and Guptill isn't totally in control of the drive, nonetheless he hits it pretty cleanly but just off the carpet and Ponting swoops at short cover and collects a good catch low down, big wicket for Australia
good channel wide of off stump and Taylor allows it through to the keeper
good length and Taylor moves forward and plays to point
back of a length and McCullum plays into the on side
good length, McCullum hops back and plays to mid on from the back foot
good corridor from Johnson and McCullum is back and leaving
full and some genuine away swing to the right hander and McCullum watches it go by and it's called wide
back of a length and outside off and he pushes into the point region
fuller on middle stump and he punches firmly to mid on
great channel to finish from Johnson and McCullum allows it through to Haddin
good channel and Taylor is happy to leave well outside off
good length on middle and Taylor pushes into the leg side to get off the mark
good length well outside off and McCullum plays and misses. It seems as though he's now ion two minds as to whether to play his natural game or not, knowing that the debutante Stewart is next in
McCullum advances and Watson bowls a wide slower ball and he leaves it alone
Watson bends his back and hits the wicket hard forcing McCullum into a back foot defensive stroke into the off side
good length but full enough to bring McCullum forward and he defends to short cover
Johnson errs on line and he strays down leg
fuller this time and Taylor drives and misses. Well bowled from Johnson as he gets the ball to shape away from Taylor
great bumper from Johnson and Taylor just sways inside the line and it really takes off and flies over Haddin for four and it's called too high. Harsh decision going against Johnson there
fuller on leg stump and Taylor is beaten, it takes him on the front pad and there is a stifled appeal but it's given not out
fuller and Taylor drives into the on side
half volley outside off stump and he drive to mid off
pitched up and far too wide of off stump
full and wide again and Taylor square drives to the off side sweeper
good channel to finish outside off stump and McCullum leaves it alone
back of a length and Taylor plays into the off side
half volley outside off and Taylor drives to Ponting at short cover
back of a length and Taylor pushes back to the bowler
good length again and Taylor plays from the crease into the off side
half volley on middle and Taylor drives firmly to White at mid wicket
back of a length and Taylor is nicely in behind it and defending into the off side. Taylor looks as though he really wants to get after it but Australia are doing a good job
good length but too straight and McCullum whips it to deep backward square
Johnson misses his line again and it takes Taylor on the thigh and falls into the leg side
short from Johnson and McCullum is into position early and pulls over deep square leg for half a dozen
better length and McCullum is in behind the line and playing to mid on
short and in at the body and McCullum fends off his rib cage from his right hand glove and into the leg side for an easy single
good length and it tails away from the right handed Taylor and takes the outside edge down to third man
good channel nips back and Taylor tries to square cut but misses, it takes him on the back pad but he's hit outside the line of off and Asad Rauf says not out
back of a length and McCullum plays back down the pitch
slower ball is shorter and wider and McCullum cuts backward of point but can't get enough on it to beat the point fieldsman
Watson hits the deck hard and defends into the off side, Voges picks it up and hits at the bowlers end but it was a well judged run and McCullum is home safe
slower ball and Taylor works it through the leg side to the sweeper

McCullum advances and seizes the moment by hammering a good length ball over cover to the short boundary for six. He hit that like a tracer bullet. Just so clean. He will need to bat for a long period today if New Zealand are to post a competitive score
fullish length and Taylor drives sweetly to Ponting at mid off, he throws it towards the stumps but wide of Haddin and they get an overthrow to fine leg
good length and McCullum plays a fraction too early and gets a leading edge into the off side
back of a length and McCullum pushes into the gap at point to the sweeper
good channel again from Harris and Taylor plays into the off side
good length and Taylor plays with soft hands into the off side for a quick single
bends his back again and McCullum pushes to Voges at point
slower ball to start from 'Catfish' Hopes and Taylor drives to point
full and outside off and Taylor square drives to deep point
good length and McCullum comes forward and pushes slightly uppishly through mid off to the man on the fence
back of a length and Taylor pushes to mid off and steals a quick single to the man on the 30m ring
good length and McCullum uses the width to guide it to third man
fuller on middle stump and driven back to the bowler. Let's have a drink
good length on off stump and McCullum plays into the off side for an easy single
Harris hits the corridor and Taylor moves back and defends off the outside half of the bat behind point for one
cracking delivery beats McCullum outside off. It seems as though there's a bit in the track if you really bend your back as Harris does every ball
too straight this time and McCullum clips it to fine leg to bring up his half-century well played
drawn forward and played to mid off for a quick single, well run
angled towards leg stump and McCullum misses, it takes him on the pad and they take a run into the leg side. Harris is adamant it deserves a closer look but the umpire isn't interested
back of a length and cut to third man
slower ball is full and Taylor tries to make something out of nothing, hitting in the air just past cover for four
full on middle and worked into the leg side
back of a length, gets Taylor high on the blade as he looks to play through the off side
fuller again and Taylor drives to White at cover
pitched up and Taylor plays to Ponting at mid wicket
tossed up on the yorker length and driven back to the bowler
full on leg stump and whipped through the leg side to deep forward square leg
fuller again and Taylor clips to mid wicket
Taylor showing a lot of frustration here as he hits straight to cover
Taylor uses softer hands this time and gets one into the off side
flatter and cut to deep point
shortish and it at the hip and clipped backward of square on the leg side for a couple to the sweeper. It was tight but well run
angled down the leg side and Haddin misses the ball and removes the bails without the ball and they get a couple to fine leg
too straight again and it takes McCullum on the hip and runs fine to fine leg
back of a length outside off and McCullum pushes into the off side
good length and McCullum plays it to third man
full on leg stick and Taylor clips it from the middle of the bat out to deep square leg where Hussey moves quickly and takes a good diving catch low down
good length and played into the off side, McCullum calls yes then immediately no
tossed up outside off and Stewart square drives to backward point
slightly shorter this time and played to backward point again
fuller and straighter and played back to the bowler
good length, spinning back into him and he pushes off the outside edge, just past the outstretched hand of first slip for a couple
straighter and he moves across his stumps and tries to play into the leg side, it takes him on the pad and runs down to fine leg
tossed up on middle and McCullum defends into the leg side
good channel but just enough width to use the pace and play to third man
slower ball back of a length and McCullum pushes towards mid on but can't beat Ponting at mid wicket
back of a length and pushed back past the bowler to long on
too straight and whipped down to fine leg
short outside off and cut hard to deep point
back of a length, Stewart drives on the up but drags it to Ponting at mid wicket
tossed up on middle and it's full enough to drive firmly to long on
Stewart comes down the track, looks to hit it straight down the ground in the air but drags it towards Watson at long on who takes the simplest of catches
short and cut nicely to deep point
tossed up and defended into the off side
fuller and Styris drives to Ponting at mid wicket
shorter this time and Styris moves back and punches towards mid on but he can't beat Johnson wh hustles well from mid wicket to save the single
good length adn McCullum pushes into the off side
good length and McCullum is nicely in behind it and defending into the off side
fuller from Bollinger and the slower ball has McCullum playing too early and hits in the air but just short of Johnson at mid off
back of a length angling across the right hander and Styris square drives to cover point
good length and Styris has found his timing immediately playing to cover point
back of a length on middle stump and Styris plays to mid on off the back foot
full and driven to mid wicket
better length and McCullum tries to play into the leg side with soft hands but can't find the gap
uses his feet and chips it straight to White at mid wicket. Poor dismissal as the pressure told and Australia are extremely happy to remove the dangerman
Vettori tries to sweep immediately and it hits him on the body and runs past Haddin on the off side
Styris gets the front foot down the track and laps it fine
Hauritz comes wide on the crease and angles into the pads and Vettori plays through the leg side
good length on off stump and Vettori still has enough width to guide it to third man
bac of a length in at the hip and Styris takes a quick single into the leg side
good length and Vettori drives on the up from the outside half of the bat to third man
great length and Styris moves back and punches to mid off
Bollinger continues to bend his back and hits the bat hard as Styris is back and defending into the off side
great corridor again from Bollinger and Styris pushes off the back foot into the off side
Vettori leans forward and sweeps from middle and off through the leg side to Hopes on the boundary at square leg
shortish and Styris moves back and cuts to short third man for a quick single
good length outside off and he plays inside out through backward point to the sweeper Bollinger who does well with White to keep the scoring to one
pitched up and dips quickly but Styris plays nicely through square leg for a single
flatter and Vettori cuts off the inside edge past Haddin into the leg side
uses his feet this time and is half-defeated in flight as he drives back past the bowler
Vettori walks across his stumps and clips to fine leg
full and driven to White at cover and he struggles to get a hand on it and misfields allowing a single
good length and Vettori waits for it and punches through the off side to the sweeper
back of a length and Styris moves back and punches into the off side
too straight and clipped to fine leg
short ball pulled ot to deep backward square, they look for two but aren't prepared to take any risks
Vettori shuffles across his stumps and clips a full ball outside off to fine leg
good length and Styris plays nicely into the leg side to rotate the strike
full inswinging delivery and Vettori misses as he tries to play to leg, Johnson appeals but it's going well down leg
full inswinger again and it takes Vettori on the pads and rolls into the leg side
fullish on middle and Styris whips it through the leg side to the sweeper
good channel outside off and Vettori drives off the inside half of the bat to fine leg
walks across his stumps again and gets an inside edge onto his pad and takes a single into the leg side
Hopes hits a good fullish length and Styris plays a fraction early, it takes a leading edge and floats back to Hopes who takes a good catch low down in his follow through
back of a length and it really flies through quickly and Hopkins is beaten outside off
bumper from Hopes and Hopkins ducks underneath it
good length draws Hopkins forward, he defends with bat and pad close together, Hopes appeals but there's too much doubt to give it out
fuller outside off and Hopkins pushes off the outside half of the blade past point for a single
good length in at the body and Hopkins is tightly in behind it and playing into the leg side
in at the body again but too straight and he whips it off his hip to fine leg
inswinging yorker and Vettori walks across his stumps and clips it to backward square
full and swings into Vettori who stays on the crease and is trapped dea in front, no problems giving that out for umpire Baxter, that was very adjacent
Johnson bends his back and forces Franklin back immediately and defending into the off side
fuller this time and driven to mid off
good length, Hopkins comes forward and plays to cover
full and driven through the gap at point to the sweeper. New Zealand need a partnership here because in the last 10-15 overs they have folded faster than Superman on laundry day
full outside off and Franklin drives firmly through the covers for a couple
better length this time and Franklin pushes through the covers to the sweeper
short and at the body and Hopkins plays it around the corner to fine leg
back of a length and Franklin stands tall and punches to mid wicket
half volley on off and Hopkins plays nicely to mid off
fuller again outside off and Hopkinds drives without any timing to mid off
full again and wider of off stump and Hopkins drives but misses, well bowled
pitched up again and Hopkins drives off the outside half of the bat to third man
bumper angled down leg but it's just close enough to Franklin not to be called wide
half volley crunched straight to mid off
good length outside off and Hopkins pushes into the off side
back of a length and played back to the bowler
good length draws Hopkins forward and he uses the pace to play to third man
fullish length and Franklin pushes his hands at the ball and plays to point
Hopes hits the wicket hard and Franklin is solid and punching to mid off
fraction too straight and Franklin works it through the leg side
good length outside off and Franklin drives on the up to cover
back of a length and Franklin drives off the inside edge back to the bowler
full and driven sweetly to mid off
good length and Franklin drags the drive into the leg side
back of a length on off stump and Franklin plays back to the bowler
good length to finish and Franklin moves back and punches through mid wicket for a single
angled into middle stump and clipped to mid wicket
good delivery angled back into middle stump, Franklin drives but misses and is taken high on the back leg
good channel and he beats Franklin outside off stump, great delivery
fuller this time and driven to long on
this one really takes off and beats Hopkins, the bowler and keeper go up but there's no edge or deviation
good length and Hopkins plays off the inside half of the bat to the on side
tossed up on leg stump and played towards mid on but Hauritz moves quickly to field
short into the pads and whipped through square leg
tossed up and Hopkins uses his feet and drives strongly to Hussey at deep point and they have enough time to complete two
flatter and Hopkins punches off the back foot through point to the man on the fence
quicker and angled down leg and Franklin rolls with it, playing to fine leg
good length outside off turning back into the batsman and he squeezes it into the off side for a quick single to short fine leg
back of a length and he uses the pace and plays to third man
good length and driven to mid off for a quick single
good length again and Hopkins pushes back along the pitch
bumper from Hopes and it's too high and just down the leg side so called wide
good length narrowing into off stump and Hopkins pushes through cover point to the sweeper
angled into leg stick and Franklin misses, it takes him on the pad and they take a leg bye into the leg side
Hopes bowls back of a length and Hopkins pushes into the off side but can't pick the gap
tossed up on off and pushed into the off side for a single
tossed up outside off and this one bites, takes the inside edge of the bat and rolls into the leg side

Franklin goes down on one knee and tries to sweep a ball that is down the leg side, he gets a glove on it and drags it back onto the stumps. That is unlucky but when things aren't goin so well those things tend to go against you
full and swept through forward square leg for a single to the man in the deep
tossed up and driven to long on
nicely flighted and Tuffey defends back to the bowler
back of a length and Hopkins gets underneath it and ramps it over backward point for four
good length and Hopkins pushes to point
slightly fuller and straighter and Hopkins plays nicely into the leg side through mid wicket to the man on the rope
good length on middle and off and played into the off side

back of a length from Watson and Tuffey sits back and pullspwerfully over id wicket for six! That is an amazing stroke from a decent length delivery. I think everyone at the ground is as surprised as me
fuller this time and Tuffey pushes into mid wicket to retain the strike
short and cut backward of point to the man on the fence
tossed up and driven through the off side to long off
flatter again and Tuffey moves back and drvies off the back foot through cover for a couple to Hussey on the boundary
fuller again from Hauritz, Tuffey goes down on one knee and sweeps over deep backward square for six
shorter and flatter from Hauritz and Tuffey is seeing is so clearly he moves back and pulls over the same region for six more
full and wide of off stump, Tuffey goes down on one knee and slog sweeps straight down the ground fro six more. That's three in a row for the big fella! Sensational stuff
back of a length and Hopkins tries to play square into the off side but it takes the outside edge and through to Haddin. Crucial breakthrough as it's the first ball of the Batting Power Play
good length and Bond tries to play square into the off side with an open face and he misses
fullish and Bond plays into the leg side to get underway
yorker and Tuffey drives to cover
yorker dug out into the on side
low full toss and Tuffey clips him backward of square on the leg side for four, super stroke and great timing
full outside off from Johnson and Bond pushes the bat at it, it comes off the middle and runs backward of point for four
fullish length and he pushes through the off side to the man on the fence at point
back of a length outside off and he plays and misses
fullish length on middle and he works it through mid wicket for one
Bond pushes back into the leg side, Johson runs to retrieve it, he picks it up and throws at the non-strikers stumps but misses and goes for five
good bumper and Tuffey tries to pull, gets it high on the blade, it loops into the leg side and Haddin can't quite make enough ground to get under the catch
good length ball, Bond leans back and clubs it straight over the bowlers' head for half a dozen. What a stroke!
full on off and he pushes into the off side for an easy single with the men inside the circle back on the edge

half volley and Tuffey cracks it back at Harris and he twists in his follow through to take a superb grab and Tuffey's cameo is over. That is a superb cacth from Harris, you just can't keep him out of the action, nor the wickets
goes for the yorker, just misses his length and Southee clips it through mid wicket to the man on the fence
yorker dug out to third man
short ball and Southee sees it early and pulls but he misses

pitched up on off stump, Bond tries to hit it over mid on but gets it low on the bat and Hauritz moves forward and takes a good catch at ground level and New Zealand are bowled out for the third consecutive match

inn2.comm: Bond starts up fo New Zealand and there's a hint of inswing and he started it too straight and it goes down the leg side
good length from Bond and it hurries Watson up as he tries to guide it to third man, it seams back and hits the end of the handle
a fraction shorter and Watson tries to pull but misses, it takes him on the body and rolls into the off side towards third man
Bond strikes! Good length delivery shapes slightly back into Haddin, he stands on the crease and Haddin pushes away from the body and edges to Styris at second slip. Important wicket for the hosts
good length outside off and Ponting is back and leaving it alone, good carry through to the keeper
he draws Ponting forward and he shows good intent, defending into the off side
Bond gets this one to hoop back into Ponting and he makes an early decision to leave it alone and it flies past the off stump. The crowd are really up for this!
good start from Southee as he hits a good length, just full enough to drive and Watson crunches it to mid off on the up
better length this time and a fraction straighter has Watson defending solidly into the on side
Southee throws this one up there and it swings nicely away, taking the outside edge and racing away to third man
back of a length and Ponting moves back and punches through mid wicket for three, superb stroke
Southee hits a good length and shapes it away nicely, getting Watson to play but it beats the outside edge
full again from Southee and Watson tries to drive but it takes the inside edge and rolls out through square leg to the sweeper who comes in off the fence to collect
146 kph, Bond charges in with the crowd behind him and hits a good channel and Watson leaves it alone outside off
this one is fuller and tails back into the right hander and Watson is solid in defence
good channel and Watson plays it nicely, defending off the face of the bat and it beats third man for four
back of a length and hitting the deck hard and Watson is happy to let it go through to the keeper
slightly fuller this time but still on a good length along the same channel outside off and Watson leaves it alone
good channel from Bond but he doesn't get Watson to play, as he leaves it through to the keeper once again, good batting
fullish delivery and swinging away Ponting lunges forward and pushes through the covers for four, immaculate timing from the skipper
back of a length and it beats Ponting on the inside of his bat just wide of off stump
good length and Ponting moves back and punches to cover off the back foot
impeccable length from Southee and Ponting lunges forward, with adrenaline pumping through his veins, and defends back to the bowler off the inside edge
good length again, splices Ponting on the drive and he collects the ball on the off side
Southee drops a fraction short and Ponting is onto it in a flash and pulling backward of square for four, classy stroke and you just can't afford to drop short to this man
good channel wide of off stump and Watson leaves it alone
full in length closer to off and Watson pushes into the off side field
good length and Watson plays nicely to third man
good fullish length outside off and he pushes into the covers
back of a length outside off and Ponting moves back and drives off the inside edge just past the off stump and through to fine leg for four
fullish length and Ponting is forward and playing into the off side
Tuffey hits his length straight away and Watson punches to short cover off the back foot
good length but the lack of pace gives Watson time to use the pace and play to third man
back of a length but the lack of pace allows Ponting to rock back and pull gloriously backward of square for four more, just so elegant to watch
slower ball from Tuffey hits a good length and Ponting allows it through to the keeper
back of a length it nips back into him and beats the bat, hits him on the pads dead in front and the whole stadium goes up but Umpire Rauf says not out
the frustration shows as Tuffey loses his line and bowls down leg
good length on off and Ponting works it into the leg side through mid wicket and he's waited it well enough to take two, well played
back of a length and Watson waits for it and pushes into the gully
good length agan jst wide of off stump and Watson plays to Styris in the gully
in the channel wide of off and Watson uses the pace to play to third man
a fraction fuller and wide of off, Ponting comes forward and punches on the up superbly through point for four, that  just a remarkable cricket shot
Bond goes for the yorker and Ponting digs it out to Vettori at mid off
slower ball from Bond, Ponting doesn't pick it, tries to pull and misses
full and driven sweetly to mid off
fullish length at middle stump and Watson pushes off the inside edge to mid on for a quick single
back of a length and Ponting plays on the up to point
good length but too straight and clipped through the leg side to Stewart on the mid wicket boundary

Ponting advances and hits Tuffey straight back over his head for six. He didn't time it perfectly but he got it well enough to drop just over the rope. Tuffey must be finding this hard to handle after it looked as though he had him LBW just two overs back
good length and Ponting drives on the up to mid off
too full from Southee and Watson makes him pay by gapping it perfectly through the covers for four, that's just all class
shortish delivery and Watson moves back quickly and pulls off the bottom edge back onto his pad
good length and wide and Watson square drives beautifully through backward point for four
good length and Watson pulls off the bottom edge, it just misses his stumps and runs away for four
god length but just enough width for Watson to guide it fine of third man for four
better channel this time draws Watson forward and he defends into the off side
angled down the leg side and he clips it fine for four past short fine leg

back of a length and Ponting pushes back and punches through the off side field for four, that is just outstanding batting from the Austalian captain. New Zealand being taught a lesson tonight. This is a batting master class
good channel and Ponting plays late to third man
slower ball from Tuffey and Watson adjusts nicely, pulling past the man on the 45 for four
good length and he defends into the on side and steals a quick single to mid on
good length on middle stump and Ponting gets an inside edge back onto his pad as he takes his bottom hand off the blade trying to play into the leg side
angled bak into Watson from arod he wicket, it hits pad then bat and rolls into the leg side. Hopkins appeals but no answer given
tossed up and defended back along the pitch
full in length, it hits Watson pn the toe then he plays into the off side
slower this time and well flighted and he pushes into the on side
slighter flatter and quicker and Watson tries to cut, it slides on this wet surface and he plays to short third man
tossed up nd this delivery grips a fraction beating the bat and taking Watson on the body
full on middle and leg and Ponting clips it through the leg side to the sweeper
low full toss and Watson plays nicely through mid wicket to Tuffey on the fence
too short from Styris at his pace and Ponting moves back and swivells, playing the pull for four through long leg
rolls his fingers across this one and Ponting waits and then pulls to fine leg
god channel and Watson uses the pace to play to short third man
back of a length, it draws Watson forward into a defensive shot into the on side
tossed up and Ponting pushes to mid on and gets one

the arm ball strikes for Vettori as Watson is defeated in flight, he moves back and it takes him below the knee roll dead in front and Umpire Baxter raises his finger. Important breakthrough for the hosts
well flighted, it draws White into a solid defensive shot into the on side
nicely flighted on off stump and White is forward and defending into the off side field
tossed up and pushed into the off side
slightly quicker in a middle and leg and White pushes with hard hands back past the bowler to mid on
full on middle and Ponting walks across his stumps and plays to mid wicket
good length and Ponting pushes back and drives off the back shoe to long on
good length n off and White plays back to the bowler
good channel and White defends off the inside half of the blade to mid on
decent length, a fraction short, White plays off the back foot to mid off, nice stroke
Styris rolls his fingers across it and White pushes to mid on looking for a single

well flighted and it pitches in line with middle and straightens nicely, Ponting is defeated, it hits him on the pad and Umpire Baxter takes his time but gives that out. New Zealand have a sniff here.
the arm ball straight away and Voges doesn't pick it as he tries to cut but it beats the bat
